ratings.question_text: Overall, how would you rate the workload of this course in comparison to other Yale courses you have taken?
What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: A ton of work; ate up my weekly schedule. By far the most time-demanding class I took this semester. Do it if you want credit for research.
this is a great opportunity to spend time doing what you find interesting!

Good for getting research experience. Really try to get into a good lab (ie, One where you will be mentored adequately). It is less important what you are researching and more important the people you will be taught by and the PI.
